  "prompt": "Which guitar should I buy in range of 7 to 8k?",
  "response": "Selecting the right guitar within a budget of \u20b97,000 to \u20b98,000 depends on your preferred type (acoustic, electric, or classical) and your experience level. Below are some highly recommended options across different categories that offer great value for money within your budget:\n\n### **Acoustic Guitars**\n\n1. **Yamaha F310**\n   - **Description:** A popular choice for beginners, the Yamaha F310 offers a balanced tone with a sturdy build. It's known for its comfortable playability and reliable performance.\n   - **Key Features:**\n     - Spruce top with meranti back and sides\n     - Slim neck for easy handling\n     - Durable construction ideal for learning\n\n2. **Fender FA-100**\n   - **Description:** Fender is renowned for quality guitars, and the FA-100 is no exception. It provides a rich sound and comes with a variety of accessories, making it a great starter pack.\n   - **Key Features:**\n     - Laminated spruce top\n     - Gloss finish for enhanced aesthetics\n     - Includes a gig bag, strap, and picks\n\n3. **Cort AD810**\n   - **Description:** Cort guitars are known for their craftsmanship, and the AD810 offers excellent sound quality with a sleek design. It's suitable for both beginners and intermediate players.\n   - **Key Features:**\n     - Solid spruce top\n     - Rich, resonant sound\n     - Comfortable neck profile\n\n### **Electric Guitars**\n\n1. **Squier by Fender Affinity Stratocaster**\n   - **Description:** This guitar offers the classic Stratocaster design with reliable performance. It's perfect for beginners looking to explore various genres.\n   - **Key Features:**\n     - Three single-coil pickups\n     - Comfortable \"C\" shaped neck\n     - Versatile tone suitable for multiple styles\n\n2. **Yamaha Pacifica Series PAC012**\n   - **Description:** Yamaha Pacifica guitars are celebrated for their quality and affordability. The PAC012 model is great for those starting out in electric guitar playing.\n   - **Key Features:**\n     - HSS pickup configuration (Huey, Single, Single)\n     - Alder body for a balanced tone\n     - Smooth maple neck with rosewood fretboard\n\n3. **Ibanez GRX20**\n   - **Description:** Ibanez offers sleek designs and solid performance. The GRX20 is ideal for beginners and intermediate players looking for good value.\n   - **Key Features:**\n     - Double locking tremolo system\n     - Super 58 humbuckers for versatile sound\n     - Ergonomic body shape for comfort\n\n### **Classical Guitars**\n\n1. **Yamaha C40**\n   - **Description:** A staple for classical guitarists, the Yamaha C40 offers a warm, rich sound with excellent build quality, making it suitable for both beginners and advancing players.\n   - **Key Features:**\n     - Nato/Okume back and sides\n     - Carbon fiber reinforced neck for stability\n     - Comfortable neck profile for ease of play\n\n2. **Kadence Citizen**\n   - **Description:** Kadence guitars are known for their affordability without compromising quality. The Citizen model is perfect for beginners exploring classical guitar.\n   - **Key Features:**\n     - Laminated spruce top\n     - Traditional classical build\n     - Comes with a gig bag and accessories\n\n### **Additional Considerations**\n\n- **Accessories:** Depending on the guitar you choose, you might need to purchase additional accessories such as a tuner, capo, extra strings, and a sturdy gig bag or case.\n  \n- **Local Availability:** Prices and availability can vary based on your location. It's advisable to visit local music stores to try out the guitars or check reputable online retailers that offer good return policies.\n\n- **Warranty and Support:** Ensure that the guitar comes with a warranty and that the brand offers good customer support in your region.\n\n### **Final Tips**\n\n- **Try Before You Buy:** If possible, visit a store to play different models. Personal comfort and how the guitar feels in your hands are crucial.\n  \n- **Read Reviews:** Look for user reviews and professional opinions to gauge the quality and performance of the guitar model you're interested in.\n\n- **Consider Future Upgrades:** Choose a guitar that not only fits your current needs but also offers room for growth as you advance in your playing skills.\n\nBy considering these options and tips, you should be able to find a guitar that fits your budget and meets your musical aspirations. Happy playing!",
